In Simple Version Control for files we have included the following command line options:

1) svc 'filename'
	To display current version of file 'filename'
	
2) svc 'filename' -v 'v' 
	To know the version 'v' of file 'filename'
	
3) svc 'filename' -a 'characters'
	To append 'characters' to file 'filename'
	
4) svc -d 'number'
	To delete line number 'number' from file 'filename'
	
5) svc -r 'v'
	To revert back to version 'v'
	
6) svc -h
	To display help options
